libuna is a library to support Unicode and ASCII (byte string) conversions.

Project information:

* Status: alpha
* Licence: LGPLv3+

Supported encodings:

* 7-bit ASCII
* ISO-8859-1, ISO-8859-2, ISO-8859-3, ISO-8859-4, ISO-8859-5, ISO-8859-6, ISO-8859-7, ISO-8859-8, ISO-8859-9, ISO-8859-10, ISO-8859-11, ISO-8859-13, ISO-8859-14, ISO-8859-15
* KOI8-R, KOI8-U
* MacCentralEurRoman, MacCyrillic, MacRoman
* UTF-7, UTF-8, UTF-16, UTF-32
* Windows-874, Windows-932, Windows-936, Windows-949, Windows-950, Windows-1250, Windows-1251, Windows-1252, Windows-1253, Windows-1254, Windows-1255, Windows-1256, Windows-1257, Windows-1258

Work in progress:

* base 16, 32, 64
* MacJapanese, MacChineseTrad, MacKorean, MacArabic, MacHebrew, MacGreek, MacChineseSimp, MacRomanian, MacUkrainian, MacThai, MacIcelandic, MacTurkish, MacCroatian

For more information see:

* Project documentation: https://github.com/libyal/libuna/wiki/Home
* How to build from source: https://github.com/libyal/libuna/wiki/Building

